Gulf Stocks: Abu Dhabi Commercial, Aramex and Emirates NBD

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-04-27T10:39:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/gulf-stocks-abu-dhabi-commercial-national-bank-of-kuwait.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  gained
1.9 percent, the most since March 20.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General
Index (ADSMI)  increased 0.6 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.        Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank PJSC (ADCB)   surged to the
highest since October 2008, rising 5.6 percent to 2.84 dirhams.
The United Arab Emirates’ third-biggest bank by assets said
first-quarter profit more than doubled to 574.4 million dirhams
($156 million) from 218.6 million dirhams a year earlier.       Aramex PJSC (ARMX UH) increased the most since April 6,
advancing 2.7 percent to 1.92 dirhams. The Middle East’s largest
courier company said first-quarter profit increased 5 percent to
49.8 million dirhams helped by growth in Gulf markets and from
acquisitions.        Emirates NBD PJSC (EMIRATES)   surged the most since
October 2007, soaring 11 percent to 4.27 dirhams. The U.A.E.’s
biggest bank by assets is “comfortable” with repaying maturing
debt, Chief Financial Officer Surya Subramanian said. The bank
is targeting 4 percent growth in loans this year, Chief
Executive Officer  Rick Pudner  said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
